metadata.name: FREE Inge del Bracco
metadata.description:
Oh Twitter, how you've wronged me,  
Inge del Bracco, purveyor of art and culture,  
My account, a treasure trove of unique artworks,  
Surfaced by me for all to discover and nurture.

But now, silenced, my voice no longer heard,  
My account deactivated, without just cause or reason,  
Leaving my followers in the dark,  
Denied the beauty and wonder I tirelessly provide.

I implore you, Twitter, to see the error of your ways,  
To reactivate my account and let my words take flight,  
For I am but a humble messenger,  
Bringing the art world to the masses with passion and insight.

Do not let censorship prevail,  
Do not let creativity be stifled,  
For in a world full of noise,  
Art is the true voice that must be heard.

So hear me, Twitter, and do what is right,  
Reactivate my account, and let my message shine bright,  
For I am Inge del Bracco, and my love for art knows no bounds,  
And my followers deserve to see it all around.

Inge del Bracco.  
https://xyz.ingedelbracco.com  
---  
UNFORTUNATELY EARLY JANUARY 2023, OUR TWITTER ACCOUNT WAS SUSPENDED WITH NO PRIOR NOTICE AND NO EXPLANATION.
